 - 4 formas de upar intimidade 

- Capturando Regigigas na síntese de fragmentos 

- Desafio do espelho

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Alomomola
body:
594: Alomomola

Something that is somewhat known is that initially, Gen 5 wasn’t going to go with the whole soft reboot/entirely new Pokemon thing at first, and the decided on that at a later date. No Pokemon in Gen 5 makes this more obvious that Alomomola. Just look at this. How was this NOT meant to be a new evolution for Luvdisc before they decided to cut its ties to it. You’d think the same thing with Emolga and Pachirisu a bit, but the two are still a little more visually distinct from each other, so Emolga must’ve been redesigned. I can’t imagine Alomomola changed that much, if at all from its “was gonna be a Luvdisc evo” design.

I guess I kinda lied yesterday when I said all the ocean routes had were Frillish. But Alomomola makes an appearance as the sea’s Audino of sorts. Thing is I meant more like as a common encounter. Because I’d swear I’ve gone on half-a-dozen playthroughs without ever meeting a wild Alomomola because the dang things are so hard to come across, only granting I haven’t actively looked for one.

But with it possibly being obvious from its appearance, Alomomola is based on the sunfish. Otherwise known as a “mola mola.” Which is simply a great fish to be a basis for a Pokemon. Sadly though, I feel like Alomomola misses the mark a little bit. Not quite looking ridiculous or flat enough. It’s acceptable otherwise, but as a fan of that fish it’s just a bit disappointing.

Personal Score: 6.5/10

Heh.

[Archive]

caption:
31 Day Pokemon Challenge:
Day 5 - Favorite Fire Type: Talonflame!

I really enjoy Fire-types, but it wasn’t hard to pick my favorite because I’ve not been very impressed with Fire-type designs in the past. But not only is this a Fire-type that kicks ass, it’s based on one of my favorite real-life birds, the Peregrine Falcon!

He brought you a feather!
